Thursday. James Capel expects a 0.6 per cent rise in industrial production,
noting that recent rises in industrial orders point to continuing strength
in production.
It forecasts a 0.5 per cent increase in overall manufacturing orders, noting
that, encouragingly for the sustainability of the recovery, the improvement
in orders was increasingly spreading to the domestic side.
