FT  03 OCT 94 / Emerging Markets: News round-up - Morocco
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Morocco is soon to sell off its stakes in five entreprises with a total
turnover of 3.85bn dirhams (Dollars 438.4m), the Privatisation Ministry
said.
The state has between 35 and 99 per cent of the five groups - Banque
Marocaine du Commerce Exterieur (BMCE), the Simef diesel and electric motor
maker, the Sonasid steel mill, the Somas oil company and Sochepresse
publication distributor.
Since January, 12 state-owned enterprises have been sold off, officials
said.
Emerging markets coverage appears daily on the World Stock Markets page
