<HEADLINE>
FT  03 OCT 94 / Company News (This Week): Concerns cloud healthy sector -
SHK Properties
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Sun Hung Kai Properties, one of Hong Kong's leading property developers,
will post its final results on Friday, effectively winding up the colony's
reporting season.
SHK Properties boasts one of the biggest land banks in Hong Kong and the
market is looking for an annual increase in earnings of around 30 per cent
to HKDollars 8.7bn (Pounds 705m). Earnings per share are forecast to improve
23 per cent to HKDollars 3.88. This marks a deceleration on the past three
years, partially reflecting the mix of bank and government measures taken to
cool Hong Kong's overheating property market.
Results from the big property developers for last year range from a
virtually flat performance at Cheung Kong through to the 64 per cent surge
reported by Sino Land. Despite the stagnant performance, investors were
cheered by Cheung Kong's results which beat the expected 20 per cent
decline. But the developers go into their new financial year with a number
of concerns which could dent this year's healthy rises. Although the
government has called off - temporarily - its war on rocketing home prices,
bank mortgage limits remain in place while interest rates are rising.
Property prices have dropped around 10-15 per cent since April, just after
the government revealed its intention to act on rocketing home prices.
</TEXT>
