<HEADLINE>
FT  03 OCT 94 / IMF/World Bank in Madrid: Loan planned for Algeria - Madrid
Conferences Digest
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By PETER NORMAN
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
The World Bank is preparing a loan of between Dollars 100m and Dollars 200m
for Algeria to help it with an ambitious structural reform programme. Mr
Caio Koch-Weser, World Bank president for the Middle East and North Africa,
said he hoped to put the proposed 'emergency rehabilitation loan' before the
Bank board before the end of this year. In addition, the Bank was providing
an emergency Dollars 50m loan in the wake of an earthquake disaster.
