<DATELINE>
   BEIJING
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
China's steelmakers, facing rising stockpiles and falling prices at home,
plan to export more. However, exports in the first eight months of this year
totalled only 930,000m, against a target of 2m for the year. Domestic
steelmakers reduced output because of rising stockpiles.
