<HEADLINE>
FT  03 OCT 94 / World Trade News: Bombardier to provide light transit system
for Kuala Lumpur
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ROBERT GIBBENS
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   MONTREAL
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Bombardier, the Canadian aerospace and transport equipment group, and
SNC-Lavalin, Canada's biggest engineering group, will provide a CDollars
961m (Dollars 717m) 30km, 25-station light transit system for Kuala Lumpur,
for completion in 1998. Bombardier-SNC will build 70 vehicles and be
responsible for system controls and rails. Renong of Malaysia will build the
glideway and stations. Bombardier-SNC's share of the total contract is
almost CDollars 600m. The transport system will be based on Vancouver's
Skytrain.
