FT  03 OCT 94 / Vietnam exchange to open
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   HANOI
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Vietnam's first securities exchange is expected to open early next year, the
official Vietnam News Agency reported at the weekend. Quoting the central
State Bank, it said the exchange would start 'on a very small scale', with
trading in bonds issued by the government, local authorities, commercial
banks and state companies. Trading in shares of privatised state companies,
only a handful of which have so far issued stock to shareholders, will
follow later. The report confirmed that the State Bank and Finance
Ministry's joint committee on setting up the exchange intended to go ahead
despite the slow pace of privatisation. Vietnam, which currently has no
secondary markets, sees the stock exchange as a vital part of
market-oriented reforms launched in the late 1980s.
