<HEADLINE>
FT  01 OCT 94 / World Commodities Prices: Spices
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Black pepper prices shot up this week to levels not seen in many years,
reports Man Poducten. Spot supplies in Europe were almost completely
exhausted and supplies from origin were very hard to obtain. As demand for
pepper has been coming in from many consuming markets prices could not but
increase very steeply. Black pepper grade 1 was quoted at about USDollars
2,750 a tonn. The highest price paid was for Malabar MG1 at Dollars 2,975,
cif, ex-new crop, for February/March shipment. Demand for white peper
remained limited. None the less the price went up as well, to about Dollars
3,400 a tonne, cif. Here too supplies were hard to obtain.
