FT  01 OCT 94 / Briefcase, Q&amp;A: Setting losses against income
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Some time ago in the FT, I read an article saying that losses in private
managed companies can be set against income. My accountant says it does not
apply to offshore trusts. Is he correct?
The article you read was talking about sections 573 to 576 of the Income and
Corporation Taxes Act 1988. To satisfy yourself that your accountant is
right, go to a local reference library and look up these provisions in one
of the multi-volume tax works, such as the British Tax Encyclopedia.
No legal responsibility can be accepted by the Financial Times for the
answers given in these columns. All inquiries will be answered by post as
soon as possible.
