<HEADLINE>
FT  01 OCT 94 / Finance and the Family: Benefit advice line - At a glance
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Help the Aged says pensioners are missing out on state benefits worth about
Pounds 400m a year. The charity says government statistics show that about
500,000 of the poorest pensioners are eligible for income support and other
benefits, but do not claim them. Help the Aged has a free telephone advice
line to help with this and other issues affecting the elderly. Call 0800-289
404 for advice.
</TEXT>
<XX>
Countries:-
</XX>
<CN>GBZ  United Kingdom, EC.
</CN>
<XX>
Industries:-
</XX>
<IN>P7389 Business Services, NEC.
</IN>
<XX>
