<HEADLINE>
FT  01 OCT 94 / Finance and the Family: Investors favour UK equity income
funds - At a glance
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Investment in unit trusts last month rose to a net Pounds 773m from Pounds
646m in July but it was below August 1993's net investment of Pounds 981m.
Private investors accounted for 55 per cent of the total with UK equity
income funds as their favourite. The Association of Unit Trusts and
Investment Funds, which released the figures, said that the number of
unitholder accounts crossed the 6m threshold for the first time, to 6.04m.
The figure has risen by one-third since January 1992 against a background of
low interest rates, as private investors have turned to equity-related
products in the search for better returns than in the building society.
