<HEADLINE>
FT  01 OCT 94 / London Stock Exchange: Gas in demand
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The see-saw performance by British Gas shares over recent sessions continued
yesterday with further dividend upgrades by some of the market's leading
broking houses driving the shares sharply better and recapturing most of the
fall that followed Thursday's important strategy meeting.
At the close Gas shares, again the heaviest individual traded stock in the
market, were 8 1/2 higher at 298 1/2 p on turnover of 15m.
Firmer oil prices, plus Talk of renewed US and domestic buying interest
helped BP move up 6 1/2 to 399 1/2 p on 11m traded. Shell, still helped by
the recent upgrade by Nomura, jumped 11 1/2 to 698 1/2 p.
